      "Heading": "Poaching the Eggs",
      "content": "For poached eggs, add a little vinegar to a pot of water. The vinegar helps prevent the egg white from spreading too much. Crack an egg directly into the pot of barely boiling water and let it cook for 4-6 minutes, depending on your preference. Use a slotted spoon to gently lift the egg out of the water."
