      "Heading": "Peeling and Serving",
      "content": "To peel hard cooked eggs, run them under cold running water to break through the shell and remove the skin. For poached eggs, trim any excess egg white and choose the side that looks best to present. Store poached eggs in cold water until ready to serve. When an order comes in, briefly lower the egg into hot water and serve."
    },
    "step5": {
      "Heading": "Alternative Cooking Method",
